Privacy Policy for TerraRun
Last updated: January 2, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how TerraRun ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and discloses your information when you use our mobile application (the "App").

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Location Data & Movement
TerraRun is a location-based game. We collect and process your:

GPS Location: To place you on the map, determine territory capture, and verify gameplay speed. Location monitoring primarily occurs while the app is open.
Step Count: We access your device's pedometer/motion sensors to reward you for walking.

1.2 User Accounts
You create an account using your Email Address and Password. We store:
Your email address (for login and account recovery).
Your display name (username).
Your profile picture (avatar selection).
We do not access your social media accounts or contacts.

1.3 Game Data
We store your game progress, including:
Captured territories.
Score and Leaderboard ranking.
Inventory items and purchase history.

2. How We Use Your Information
To Provide the Service: To make the game work (e.g., showing you on the map).
Analytics: To understand how users play and improve the game experience.
Security: To prevent cheating (e.g., GPS spoofing) and ensure fair play.
3. Data Sharing
We do not sell your personal data.

Other Players: Your in-game username, avatar, and territory ownership are visible to other players on the map and leaderboards.
Service Providers: We use third-party services like Google Firebase (for hosting, database, and authentication) which may process data on our behalf.

4. Your Rights
You may request the deletion of your account and data at any time by contacting us or using the "Delete Account" feature within the App settings.

5. Contact Us
If you have questions about this policy, please contact us at: flamebeast64@gmail.com
